# Netlify _redirects — first match wins, top-to-bottom.
#
# Hub-install routes (PWA install: separate HTMLs each link a hub-specific
# <link rel="manifest"> so iOS Safari / Android Chrome read the right
# start_url at HTML parse time, before any JS runs). Without these, Add to
# Home Screen captures whatever manifest index.html links — which is the
# generic root manifest. The dynamic in-React applyManifestHref() helper
# stays as defensive runtime sync but is NOT relied on for install.
#
# /dailys serves the daily-reports hub (start_url=/dailys).
# /equipment serves the equipment/fueling hub (start_url=/equipment).
# /webforms is the legacy daily-reports alias.
# /fueling is the legacy equipment alias.
# Legacy aliases need their own rules so Add to Home Screen reads the right
# manifest at HTML parse time; the client-side alias in routes.js then
# navigates to the canonical path after the app boots.
/dailys          /dailys.html     200
/dailys/*        /dailys.html     200
/webforms        /dailys.html     200
/webforms/*      /dailys.html     200
/equipment       /equipment.html  200
/equipment/*     /equipment.html  200
/fueling         /equipment.html  200
/fueling/*       /equipment.html  200
# /pasture-map serves the Pasture Map field hub (start_url=/pasture-map) so the
# home-screen icon opens straight into the map and works offline in the field.
/pasture-map     /pasture-map.html  200
/pasture-map/*   /pasture-map.html  200

# SPA fallback — any other unmatched path serves index.html so client-side
# routing (React Router) can take over. Status 200 (not 301) so the browser
# URL stays as-is. MUST stay last; it's the catch-all.
/*  /index.html  200
